manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Can this external SSD work with IOS? Yes, but it can only support Type-C Port such as iPad Pro, iPhone 15, 15 Pro, 15 Pro Max, etc. Why can't this USB drive be recognized on a smartphone? Please go to check the flash drive’s format, make sure it is EXFAT and open the OTG function. Why does the write speed drop when I write to large files? If you want to maintain a high write speed, it is recommended that you do not write more than 1/4 of the remaining usable capacity at one time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast, top-quality standard-size USB thumb drive, runs hot
reviews.reviewText: As reported by others, sequential speed tests at about 90% of maximum SATA throughput.SGC's ValidDrive reports flawless performance over entire storage address range (see screenshot).The drive surprisingly runs very warm to the touch, although this may be typical of tight data packing on SSD. Even so, one should perhaps be careful to ensure adequate ventilation to cool the drive.FWIW, CrystalDiskInfo reports 54°C after an 8GB file write @25°C ambient.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars One of the best small external drives
reviews.reviewText: This is my second product from Fanxiang and I am seriously impressed by this one, and the company has come a long way since I checked out one of their 2.5'' ssd drives. Now, with this portable drive I am pleasantly surprised by the performance and quality, especially for the price. This 512 GB external drive has surprised me on several different levels, but most of all with its speed for the capacity of the drive, there are other positives and I will try to list them all below, but before that a few words about the packaging and presentation. The thumb drive comes in a very stylish little retail box, with the company name and the list of specifications of the drive, so before even opening it, you will know what you are getting. Inside the box there is the drive nested inside a protective foam shell and a small warranty card, that is it.Positives:- Surprisingly fast speed for the size and capacity - if you look at the test for the speed of the drive you will see 430Gb read and 430Gb write speeds on this small capacity drive, and those speeds are very good considering all the factors, I was surprised, in addition, those speeds a bit lower than what the company was promising, but I am still impressed by them considering the super small size.- Inexpensive - Around $40 for the 512GB USB 3.2 Gen 2 drive, this model is priced very reasonably and the quality is there to back it up.- Extremely portable, yet made of high quality metal, it can fit in any pocket and can be used with laptops, desktops, tablets and even cell phones as well, since the drive is featuring both USB-A and USB-C connections.- Easy to use - I am using this drive as a primary data transfer drive, when I need to quickly carry large files between different devices, and with the fast speeds, it can be done in minutes.- Great looking and lite, no flashy labels or RGB, good to be used for any computer - The metal body is great for heat dissipation, due to the high speeds and data transfer, the drive heats up, but the metal does a great job to absorb and dissipate. The drive feels solid and very high quality.Negatives:- No cap included on either of the ends - The way the drive is constructed to swing around the base depending on which connection you are currently using, one is remaining protected, but the other one is always exposed, so for example if you are using it constantly and you are carrying it in your pocket, there could be some dirt and other small particles that could end up inside the USB.- Not as fast as advertised, I was expecting speeds close to the 520GB advertised, but I could never reach those, regardless the drive is still plenty fast.Overall, this is a great small and fast thumb drive by Fanxiang, I really like it and I am still impressed by its quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality super fast USB drive
reviews.reviewText: This drive is a refreshing departure from some of the claims you see for similar products online these days. The quality of the drive in hand feels great. The materials feel premium. Most importantly, this drive delivers on its promises.I have attached a couple of reports to my review. A performance report that shows that the drive’s read/writes approach the capacity of a SATA interface which is approximately 550 MB/s. It was strange that the reads were slower than the writes and it probably means there is a DRAM cache on the drive to help speed up write operations, which is fine.The read speeds I got were very respectable and this is now the second fastest USB flash drive I own next to the Sandisk Extreme Pro 4TB drive which isn’t really competing with this easily pocketable USB drive.I also used software to confirm the capacity claims and this indeed is a 512GB drive. There are many fakes out there, but this actually is what it claims to be.I also love that it has both a USB-C and USB-A connector I definitely recommend this flash drive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SATA SSD transfer speeds in a USB stick!
reviews.reviewText: I've owned and used fanxiang/ranxiana mSATA SSDs in my Dell laptop in the past. And found them reliable and fast, and affordable.So, when I recognized the brand, I had no 2nd thoughts about trying their portable USB 3.2 SSD flash drive.It is essentially a SATA SSD in a USB stick. The capacity is decent at 512GB too. Can archive and/or transport a lot of photos, music files, etc. It's equipped with a USB-C interface for fast USB 3.2 specs, and a legacy USB-A 3.0/3.1 interface for older systems.The build quality of the USB stick is excellent. The cover has a satisfying 'click' as it pivots. It's all-metal body construction. I plugged it into a Win 10 Pro laptop with USB-A 3.0 ports. It is immediately recognized and Windows Explorer shows it is formatted with exFAT.I ran CrystalDiskMark on the SSD flash drive and I posted the results. Even with USB 3.0, it reached its advertised transfer rate. Sequential reads at 562 MB/sec.They only thing that I didn't like and concerned me was the significantly slow random reads at 17.4 MB/sec. Hmmm. Perhaps the unit will perform more consistent with a USB-C 3.2 interface.But the results are excellent regardless and shows it performs like a SATA SSD. No more waiting for a file dump! Great product, no more cables, no SSD enclosures, just a super compact and fast USB stick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great product offering a massive 512GB of storage and having the added flexibility of being made to fit both the traditional USB and newer USB C ports. It is lightweight and convenient, works well, reads/writes quickly and offers amazing value for money. My only slight criticism is that the swivel mechanism only protects one of the two ends at any time….so when it’s being transported, one end is always exposed and therefore liable to damage. Otherwise, a great product.

reviews.reviewTitle: とても高速で読み書きしてくれて大変重宝しています。
reviews.reviewText: 1か月半ほど使用していますがとても高速で読み書きどちらもこなしてくれて非常に満足しています。Type AもType Cも両対応でデザインもコンパクトですっきりしています。使いやすくて重宝しています。

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: …as you rotate to use it.I don’t like that only one side is protected at any one time, as if it’s supposed to be plugged in at all times.Which is not the case for a device like this.This apparently has a TBW (terabytes written) of about 300TB.Which is no issues for me because this will be written to until full and read from most.Essentially using only 490GB or so of the 300 TWB capacity. Unless I remove and add other similar files which would still be under 500GB TBW used…in that case, this should hold up for years…maybe decades?I feel like the two connections of both are used, would write to different parts of the SSD, so I’ve decided to use just the USB-A part.So the data written (in theory) is more consecutive, as opposed to all over the drive. So no defragging or optimisation is needed, which will of course eat into that ever dwindling TBW capacity that’s the bane of SSDs existence…You can read from either end, without affecting the TBW capacity.4/5 so far, and I will update this, should This not hold up to the write speeds and storage potential.

reviews.reviewTitle: TypeCにもTypeAにも対応した外付けSSD
reviews.reviewText: コネクタにTypeCとTypeAを備えた外付けSSDです。デスクトップやノートPC、スマホやタブレット等、幅広く対応できそう。USBメモリのような形状でコンパクト。そういった意味でも使い勝手が良いです。読み書き高速でちゃんとSSDです。fanxiangは中国のメーカーのようですがお勧め。ただ耐久性は不明。

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a really good and useful usb drive for now and the future.It has both USB-A and USB-C connections which is great since there are computers now that are doing away with USB-A connection altogether or putting them in more hard to reach places in favour of USB-C being more prominent, so it offers great flexibility when transferring data from one computer to another and kind of future proofs its use for the next 10yrs.Speed of transfer is about the same via both USB type connections and but both are very fast.Overall it feels well made, its works and with both USB type connections it will last much longer technology wise than USB drives with just a USB-A connection.
